quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  19,96,"Those who believe and do righteous deeds, the Most Compassionate will endear them [to His creation]<sup>26</sup>.","[26] And He will love them as well."
  19,97,"We have made this [Qur’an] easy in your language so that you may give thereby glad tidings to the righteous and warn people who are contentious.",""
  19,98,"How many generations We have destroyed before them! Do you sense a single one of them or even hear from them a whisper?",""
  20,1,"Tā Ha<sup>1</sup>","[1] See footnote 2:1"
  20,2,"We have not sent down the Qur’an to you [O Prophet] to cause you distress,",""
  20,3,"but as a reminder for those who fear Allah.",""
  20,4,"A revelation from the One Who created the earth and the high heavens.",""
  20,5,"The Most Compassionate rose over the Throne<sup>2</sup>.","[2] See footnote 7:54"
  20,6,"To Him belongs all that is in the heavens and all that is on earth, and all that is between them, and all that is beneath the soil.",""
  20,7,"Whether you speak loudly [or not], He surely knows what is secret and what is even more hidden.",""
  20,8,"Allah – none has the right to be worshiped except Him. He has the Most Beautiful Names.",""
  20,9,"Has there come to you the story of Moses?",""
  20,10,"When he saw a fire, he said to his family, “Stay here. I have spotted a fire; I may bring you a flaming brand from it, or find some guidance at the fire<sup>3</sup>.”","[3] They lost their way in the dark while traveling from Midian to Egypt."
  20,11,"When he came to it, he was called, “O Moses,",""
  20,12,"Indeed, I am your Lord, so take off your shoes; you are in the sacred valley of Tuwā.",""
